returns.status: The current status of the game.

params._fromSquare: The starting square index (0-63, a1=0, h1=7, a8=56, h8=63).
params._promotionPieceType: The piece type to promote a pawn to (e.g., ChessLogic.W_QUEEN). Use ChessLogic.EMPTY (0) if not a promotion.

params._opponent: The address of the player to invite (player2, Black).

returns.gameId: The ID of the newly created game.

decodeState(uint256).notice: Helper view function to decode a state for off-chain use or debugging.

getGameInfo(uint256).notice: Helper view function to get game details.

getGameState(uint256).notice: Gets the current encoded state of a game.

makeMove(uint256,uint8,uint8,uint8).notice: Makes a move in an active game. Checks for checkmate/stalemate after the move.

startGame(address).notice: Starts a new chess game with the caller as player1 (White) and the specified opponent as player2 (Black).
